SIMPLE: sixth
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sixth
<hw>Sixth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From Six: cf. AS.
<ets>sixta</ets>, <ets>siexta</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>First after
the fifth; next in order after the fifth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Constituting or being one of six equal parts into
which anything is divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1348 --></p>

<p><ent>Sixth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sixth
<hw>Sixth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quotient
of a unit divided by six; one of six equal parts which form a
whole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The next in order after the fifth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>The interval embracing six
diatonic degrees of the scale.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sixthly</ent>⟦br⟧
